From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@openai.com>
Date: Sat, 18 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] p2: co-locate CPython startup hot path

Keep the measured lifecycle and configuration translation units in one
90-KiB-safe group, pin the allocator frontends and startup-hot thread services
in Hub, and expose bounded startup stage markers for HIL diagnosis.  CPython
configuration allocates and queries thread-local state repeatedly; crossing
the single Hub execution slot for each of those calls otherwise reloads the
large configuration caller on every return even when automatic groups
preserve translation-unit locality.
